<rss version="2.0" xmlns:content="http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/" xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" xmlns:ss="http://contenthub.aol.com/slideshow/"><channel><title><![CDATA[Engadget is a web magazine with obsessive daily coverage of everything new in gadgets and consumer electronics]]></title><link/> https://www.engadget.com/ <description><![CDATA[Engadget is a web magazine with obsessive daily coverage of everything new in gadgets and consumer electronics]]></description><language> zh-CN</language><copyright>版权所有雅虎 2023</copyright><pubDate> Mon, 05 Jun 2023 19:13:28 +0000</pubDate><generator>雅虎 http://yahoo.com </generator><item><title><![CDATA[Apple's Optic ID will let you log in to the Vision Pro headset with your eyes]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p> Apple 的<a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/the-vision-pro-is-apples-long-awaited-arvr-headset-182725385.html">Vision Pro 耳机</a>将在公司产品中引入一种新的安全方法：您的眼睛。混合现实设备<a data-i13n="elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Apple;elmt:;cpos:2;pos:1" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=4130e2f0-a14f-4c5e-bdab-cd52ac7d8e79&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Apple&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAb3dJkWk3uphg-gowcxCqBMtS9W5A_O8dyGi8_d0vcRj&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.apple.com%2Fnewsroom%2F2023%2F06%2Fintroducing-apple-vision-pro%2F" class="rapid-with-clickid">将使用</a><a data-i13n="cpos:3;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/apple-mixed-reality-headset-iris-scanning-153036223.html">之前传闻的</a>Optic ID 系统，该系统通过不可见的 LED 光照射来研究您的虹膜，并将其与您注册的眼睛数据进行比较以登录。您可以将其用作密码替换并在应用程序中进行购买存储或使用 Apple Pay。</p><p>该公司强调，您的眼睛数据在耳机的 Secure Enclave 中被加密和隔离。它永远不会离开设备并且对应用程序不可用。与 Face ID 和 Touch ID 一样，不会有实际图像或入侵者滥用原始信息的方式。</p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><p> Optic ID 与 Vision Pro 耳机中的其他隐私保护一起提供。 Apple 和其他任何人都无法访问眼动追踪数据。摄像头和传感器数据在系统级别进行处理，因此应用程序不会仅仅为了启用空间功能而窥视您的周围环境。如果您正在拍摄照片和视频，将会有一个视觉指示器提醒您周围的人。您可能不必担心<a data-i13n="cpos:4;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/2016-11-17-snapchat-spectacles-hands-on.html">谷歌眼镜式的公愤</a>。</p><p>虹膜扫描并不是一个新的安全概念。例如，三星在其<a data-i13n="cpos:5;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/2016-08-16-samsung-galaxy-note-7-review.html">命运多舛的 Galaxy Note 7</a>中引入了虹膜登录。不过，对于耳机来说，这是一个相对新颖的想法，如果您不想伸手去拿键盘（真实的或虚拟的）来开始使用您的耳机或特定的应用程序，我们将不胜感激。考虑到 Apple 的目标，这一点尤为重要：它将 Vision Pro 视为“空间计算”平台的开始，您可以在混合现实中花费数小时，而 Optic ID 等便利设施可能会使该平台更具吸引力。</p><p><a data-i13n="cpos:6;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/tag/wwdc-2023/"><em>在此处</em></a><em>关注 Apple WWDC 2023 的所有新闻</em><em>。</em></p>本文最初出现在 Engadget 上，网址为 https://www.engadget.com/apple-vision-pro-headset-will-use-your-eyes-to-sign-in-with-optic-id-191328667.html?src =rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/apple-vision-pro-headset-will-use-your-eyes-to-sign-in-with-optic-id-191328667.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> efb7e233-d927-40a0-bf70-f30e3382ff0c</guid><dc:creator>乔恩·芬加斯</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>Engadget</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder> Engadget</dc:rightsholder><pubDate> Mon, 05 Jun 2023 19:13:28 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1685995067</ingested><modified> 2023-06-05T19:57:51+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[Information Technology]]></category><category><![CDATA[Software]]></category><category><![CDATA[Technology & Electronics]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Jon Fingas]]></category><media:content height="1280" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-06/af1de9a0-03d3-11ee-bdfe-42b5831ea29f" width="1920"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:descripti